# Per-release SBOMs land here automatically via the watchtower-installer
# GitHub Actions workflow on every successful build.
#
# Each file is the full `pip freeze` output captured AFTER all build
# dependencies (PyInstaller + agent runtime + cairosvg + their transitive
# closure) have been installed on the windows-latest runner. That's
# everything that gets baked into the published Watchtower-Setup.exe.
#
# Filename: v<semver>.txt (e.g. v0.14.52.txt).
#
# Audit usage:
#   - "Did we ship CVE-2024-XXXXX-vulnerable-pkg in any released version?"
#     -> grep "vulnerable-pkg==" watchtower/sboms/*.txt
#   - "What was in v0.14.52?" -> cat watchtower/sboms/v0.14.52.txt
#
# Don't edit these files manually -- they're written by the workflow.
